The results are summarized in Table~\ref{high-z SFRs} and Figure~\ref{lowz trend highz SFRs} gives a comparison of the various SFR indicators.  We draw two main conclusions.  First, the SFRs derived from the various PAH bands are generally consistent, indicating no significant change in their relative strengths with redshift.  Second, the values derived from the PAH features are generally consistent with those from the other two indicators, typically within 0.3 dex (a factor of two).  Moreover, in all cases the PAH luminosities have smaller uncertainties than the {\hbox{Pa$\alpha$}}\ measurements.  This is because the PAH features are intrinsically brighter, and they will be among the brightest SFR indicators available for cosmologically distant galaxies.

